.TH "ecryptfs_write_lower_page_segment" 9 "ecryptfs_write_lower_page_segment" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ecryptfs_write_lower_page_segment \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ecryptfs_write_lower_page_segment
.BI "(struct inode *ecryptfs_inode "  ","
.BI "struct page *page_for_lower "  ","
.BI "size_t offset_in_page "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ecryptfs_inode" 12
The eCryptfs inode
.IP "page_for_lower" 12
The page containing the data to be written to the
lower file
.IP "offset_in_page" 12
The offset in the \fIpage_for_lower\fP from which to
start writing the data
.IP "size" 12
The amount of data from \fIpage_for_lower\fP to write to the
lower file
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Determines the byte offset in the file for the given page and
offset within the page, maps the page, and makes the call to write
the contents of \fIpage_for_lower\fP to the lower inode.

Returns zero on success; non-zero otherwise
